    associative). To do transformation ``A`` followed by ``B`` is ``B * A``.

    Transforms support the buffer protocol, meaning that they can be converted
    to numpy arrays::

        >>> numpy.asarray(Transform(2., 0., 1.,
        ...                         0., 1., 2.))
        array([[2., 0., 1.],
